# Work-scoped branches

## Sync `main` before you branch

Before substantive implementation (anything beyond a one-line typo the user explicitly names):

1. **Update local `main` from the remote** so the branch base matches what reviewers will merge into:
   - `git fetch origin main`
   - `git checkout main` (or `git switch main`)
   - `git merge --ff-only origin/main`  
     If fast-forward is not possible, stop and ask how to reconcile local `main` (do not merge unrelated work into the task branch blindly).

2. **Create the task branch from that tip** (see naming below), for example:  
   `git checkout -b <scope>/<short-kebab-description> main`

If the user explicitly names a different integration branch as the base, use that instead of `main`, but still **fetch and fast-forward that branch from `origin`** before branching.

Do **not** start a new implementation task on a long-lived local branch without first updating `main` (or the agreed base) and either creating a fresh branch from it or rebasing the existing task branch onto the updated base, so pull requests stay small and merge conflicts stay rare.

---

Before substantive implementation, **create a dedicated branch** from the updated base (default **`main`**, unless the user specifies otherwise).

## Naming

Use: **`<scope>/<short-kebab-description>`** (lowercase, hyphens).

## Scopes (pick one primary scope per branch)

| Scope | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| `knowledge-graph/` | `docs/lat.md` wiki, wikilink graph, `docs/knowledge-graph-view/`, parser, tests, `graph:view` / `graph:check` |
| `platform/` | CI, git hooks, `package.json` scripts, TypeScript/Vitest config, repo automation |
| `docs/` | Documentation outside the lat graph when it is the main change |
| `feat/` | Product features (application behavior) when not covered above |
| `fix/` | Bug fixes |
| `chore/` | Mechanical maintenance only when no scope above fits |

Keep **one coherent class of work** per branch. Split unrelated changes.

## Examples

- `knowledge-graph/expose-graph-json-api`
- `platform/pre-push-verify-tuning`
- `feat/org-model-ingest-endpoint`
